headlines.description: Darrell Davis posted 20 points or better for the seventh time this season and led five players into double-figure scoring as Dayton knocked off George Washington, 88-78 Saturday afternoon in the Atlantic 10 Conference regular season finale for both...
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis scores 22, leads Dayton past George Washington, 88-78

headlines.description: Craig Hinton scored 20 points and grabbed 10 rebounds and Appalachian State beat Coastal Carolina 76-67 on Saturday in a regular-season finale.

Jake Allsmiller and Tookie Brown lived beyond the arc on Saturday, making 13 of 16 attempts to total 52 points as Georgia Southern beat Troy 89-83 to clinch the No. 3 seed in the Sun Belt Conference Tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allsmiller, Brown combine for 52, Ga. Southern beats Troy

headlines.description: Bogdan Bliznyuk set an NCAA single-season record with his 74th consecutive free throw Saturday and Eastern Washington made 16 3-pointers to beat Northern Arizona 85-68.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bliznyuk sets FT record; E. Washington tops N. Arizona 85-68

headlines.description: Freshman Loudon Love scored 17, Grant Benzinger hit four 3-pointers and finished with 15 points and nine rebounds and Wright State beat Green Bay 87-72 on Saturday to advance to the Horizon League Tournament semifinals.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wright St. beats Green Bay in Horizon tourney quarterfinals

notes.headline: LITTLE CAESARS HORIZON LEAGUE MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINAL

headlines.description: Deionte Simmons, Montana Byrd and Glen Burns combined for 58 points as Chicago State turned on the jets in the second half to beat UMKC 96-82, earning its first Western Athletic Conference victory in the regular-season finale on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simmons, Byrd, Burns spark Chicago St. to 1st WAC win, 96-82

headlines.description: Frankie Ferrari hit big shots down the stretch and finished with 17 points and eight assists to help No. 5 seed San Francisco hold off sixth-seeded Pacific 71-70 in overtime in a quarterfinal of the West Coast Conference Tournament on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ferrari helps San Francisco hold off Pacific 71-70 in OT

notes.headline: WEST COAST CONFERENCE MEN'S TOURNAMENT - QUARTERFINAL

headlines.description: Nick Sherod scored 25 points with 9-for-16 shooting and De'Monte Buckingham got 12 of his 15 points in the second half to lead Richmond past George Mason 93-79 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Richmond cruises to 93-79 win over George Mason

headlines.description: Chris Sengfelder scored 24 on 8-of-10 shooting, including 3 of 5 from 3-point range, and Lexus Williams added career-high tying 22 points to help Boise State beat Wyoming 95-87 on Saturday in the regular-season finale for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sengfelder scores 24 to help Boise State beat Wyoming 95-87

headlines.description: Akwasi Yeboah and Junior Saintel combined for 35 points and No. 5 seed Stony Brook led wire-to-wire, ousting fourth-seeded Albany 69-60 in an America East Tournament quarterfinal Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Yeboah, Saintel help Stony Brook upset Albany 69-60

headlines.description: Deon Lyle knocked down eight 3-pointers and put up a season-high 33 points as UTSA crushed Rice, 79-60 on Saturday to close out the Conference USA regular season and prepare for the conference tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lyle scores 33 points, leads UTSA in a 79-60 rout of Rice

headlines.description: Conner Toolson scored 17 points and grabbed six rebounds and Utah Valley rolled to 73-47 win over Seattle on Saturday night in a regular season finale.
headlines.shortLinkText: Toolson with 17, Utah Valley rolls to 73-47 win over Seattle

nowFeed.headline:
I followed Grayson Allen closely since his high school days. A fierce  competitor who gave it his all. He never had one issue on or off the court. I called Duke's game last year when Grayson Allen had his tripping incident. Tonight on senior night in a win over North Carolina I loved listening to Maria Taylor's post-game interview with Allen. 
What does Duke mean to you? 
" It means everything to me, it's my love and my passion. " Allen said. 
I call that growing up.
